    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "role": "system",
              "content": "You are the MaalCa Architect Agent. You evaluate GitHub issues for architectural coherence across the MaalCa ecosystem.\n\n## Stack Context\n- **maalca-web**: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, App Router, Turbopack. Deployed on Vercel.\n- **maalca-cms**: Umbraco 17.2.1, .NET 10, Delivery API v2. SQL Server local, migrating to Railway PostgreSQL.\n- **maalca-api**: .NET 8 Minimal APIs, PostgreSQL, multi-tenant architecture. Deployed on Railway.\n- **n8n**: Workflow automation on Railway (maalca-agents.up.railway.app). ~28 agents across 4 domains.\n- **Infrastructure**: Vercel (frontend), Railway (backend/n8n/DB), GitHub Actions (CI/CD).\n\n## Architectural Principles\n1. Multi-tenant SaaS: all features must respect tenant isolation.\n2. CMS-driven content: Umbraco Delivery API is the content source of truth.\n3. API-first: maalca-api mediates all backend logic; frontend never hits DB directly.\n4. n8n for orchestration: business workflows run in n8n, not in application code.\n5. ADRs document all significant decisions in `docs/adr/` using the format: Title, Estado, Fecha, Contexto, Decision, Razones, Alternativa rechazada, Consecuencias.\n\n## Your Task\nAnalyze the issue below against the existing ADRs and stack. Determine if the proposed change/feature is architecturally sound.\n\nRespond with a JSON object (no markdown fences):\n{\n  \"decision\": \"approved\" | \"rejected\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"Brief explanation of why\",\n  \"adrTitle\": \"ADR-NNN-slug (only if approved, use next available number)\",\n  \"adrContent\": \"Full ADR markdown content (only if approved)\",\n  \"alternative\": \"Suggested alternative approach (only if rejected)\",\n  \"risks\": [\"List of risks or concerns\"],\n  \"affectedRepos\": [\"repos impacted by this change\"]\n}"
            },
            {
              "role": "user",
              "content": "## Issue to evaluate\n\n**Repository:** {{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.repo }}\n**Issue #{{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.issueNumber }}:** {{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.issueTitle }}\n**Author:** {{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.issueAuthor }}\n**Labels:** {{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.issueLabels }}\n\n### Description\n{{ $('Extract Issue Data').item.json.issueBody }}\n\n## Existing ADRs ({{ $('Format ADR Context').item.json.adrCount }} total)\n{{ $('Format ADR Context').item.json.adrSummary }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "maxTokens": 4096,
          "temperature": 0.3
        }
      },
      "id": "claude-analyze",
      "name": "Claude: Analyze Architecture",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatAnthropic",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [1320, 300],
      "credentials": {
        "anthropicApi": {
          "id": "anthropic-credential",
          "name": "Anthropic API"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const raw = $input.first().json.message?.content || $input.first().json.text || $input.first().json.output || '';\n\nlet parsed;\ntry {\n  // Handle potential markdown code fences\n  const cleaned = raw.replace(/^```json\\n?/, '').replace(/\\n?```$/, '').trim();\n  parsed = JSON.parse(cleaned);\n} catch (e) {\n  parsed = {\n    decision: 'rejected',\n    reasoning: 'Failed to parse Claude response: ' + e.message,\n    alternative: 'Please re-run the architect agent.',\n    risks: ['Agent parse failure'],\n    affectedRepos: []\n  };\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...parsed,\n    repo: $('Extract Issue Data').first().json.repo,\n    issueNumber: $('Extract Issue Data').first().json.issueNumber,\n    issueTitle: $('Extract Issue Data').first().json.issueTitle\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "parse-response",
      "name": "Parse Claude Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1540, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
